description: This file defines interfaces for private WiFi service operations, including initialization, creation, deletion, start, stop, update, and event handling of WiFi service and service nodes. It also includes relevant type definitions and external includes for WiFi event and management functionalities.

methods.name: private_service_init
methods.description: Initializes the WiFi private service with the given service structure.

methods.name: private_service_create_nodes
methods.description: Creates service nodes based on radio configuration, hardware capabilities, and service configuration.

methods.name: private_service_delete_nodes
methods.description: Deletes all service nodes associated with the given service.

methods.name: private_service_update
methods.description: Updates the WiFi service with new configuration or state.

methods.name: private_service_event
methods.description: Handles incoming events for the WiFi service.

methods.name: private_node_start
methods.description: Starts a specific WiFi service node.

methods.name: private_node_stop
methods.description: Stops a specific WiFi service node.

methods.name: private_node_update
methods.description: Updates a specific WiFi service node.

methods.name: private_node_event
methods.description: Handles events for the specified WiFi service node.
